# Database Functions


## Create database and Users

You can create database and its users from cPanel interface. To create databases and its users, please follow the procedure:

- Log in to the cPanel Interface.
- Go to "Databases" >> Click on "MySQL Databases".

```diagram

```

- Under "Create New Database" >> add the database name. Database name takes the syntax username_dbName.
- Click on "Create Database" button.

```diagram

```

- Click on "Go Back" in order to go to previous page.
- Under "MySQL users", you can add new users and their passwords.
- Click "Create User".

```diagram

```

- Click on "Go Back" in order to go to previous page.
- Under "Add User To Database" select the database and user from the drop-down menus.
- Click on "Add".

```diagram

```

- Now you can give the necessary permissions to that user on the database by selecting the appropriate boxes.
- Click on "Make changes".

```diagram

```




## How to Check / Repair a Database

- Log on to cPanel of your website
- Go to "Databases" >> Click on "MySQL Databases".
- To check a database select your database from the corresponding drop down list  under Modify Databases and the click Check DB
- To repair a database select your database from the corresponding drop down list  under Modify Databases and the click Repair DB

```diagram

```


## How to Change Database User Password

- Log on to cPanel of your website
- Go to "Databases" >> Click on "MySQL Databases".
- Scroll down. Click on the selected username under "Current Users"

```diagram

```

- In the next window fill-up the form with corresponding details and then click Change Password


```diagram

```


## Remote Database Access Hosts

- Log on to your cPanel account
- Under Databases click on Remote MySQL

```diagram

```

- Enter your remote host IP address in the text box and then click on Add Host

```diagram

```



## Access phpMyAdmin 

- Log on to your cPanel account
- Under Databases click on phpMyAdmin. It will show you the phpmyadmin interface. You can manage your database records from there.

```diagram

```


## Manage MySQL Database Through phpMyAdmin

- Log on to your cPanel account
- Under Databases click on phpMyAdmin. It will show you the phpmyadmin interface.
- At your left hand side you should see the list of existing databases.

```diagram

```

- If you click on any database , on your right hand side pane it should show you all the tables
On the top you should see the tools such as query , import , export which can be used accordingly

```diagram

```

## Restore a MySQL Database

- Login to cPanel of your webiste
- Under Files click on Backups


- You should see a window of Restore a MySQL Database

- Click on Choose File. It will open up a window from where you need select the backup file of your database which is in .sql.gz format.

## How to change the password of a Mysql user in cPanel?

If you have already created a Mysql user under cPanel -> Mysql Databases section you may want to update its password.

 

You can complete the task through:

 

cPanel -> MySQL Databases

 

Find the MySQL Current Users list and click on the respective user.

 

A new MySQL Account Maintenance page will be opened.

 

There you can change the password by entering the old password in the first field and the new password into the next two fields. You can also use the built-in Password Generator.
